@database bugs.guide
@wordwrap
@node MAIN "Known Bugs"
@{b}Known Bugs@{ub}

The following bugs (or undocumented features) are known in this release:

1.  Using Gui-FTP on a PAL Hi-resolution screen, if your preferred monospace
    and/or proportional fonts are larger than 8 pixels high, the main window
    WILL NOT fit within the screen, the gadgets along the bottom and/or
    right of the window will be only partially displayed and will overlap
    the window borders.

2.  The program only recognises the long format directory listings produced
    by (most) UNIX operating systems. However programs or ARexx scripts can
    be written to convert unrecognised formats into this standard format.

3.  There appears to be a problem with VFAT (Windows 95) partitions mounted
    as such on a Linux host.  VFAT is an extension to normal FAT partitions
    to allow long (upto 255 characher) file names.  The names may include
    spaces - this seems to be the problem.

4.  The ARexx command 'PUT' doesn't show the file size in the progress
    dialogue.

@endnode
